3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bluefin calculates funding rates hourly using mark price deviation from the spot index, with payments between long and short positions at each settlement. The funding rate formula incorporates SOL spot price data from major exchanges with a time-weighted average to prevent manipulation. Funding payments are automatically debited or credited to traders' margin balances without requiring manual intervention. Bluefin's Sui-based architecture enables sub-second funding calculations and near-instant settlement compared to traditional perp exchanges."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","SOL","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SOL/USDT represents significant arbitrage potential due to Solana's high retail trading activity creating periodic funding rate spikes above 0.1% daily. The pair benefits from strong institutional participation on Bluefin, providing consistent liquidity depth for large funding rate arbitrage positions. Cross-chain arbitrage opportunities emerge when Bluefin's SOL funding diverges from Binance, OKX, and other major venues due to Sui ecosystem-specific demand patterns."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"SOL Funding Rate Patterns on Bluefin"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SOL funding rates on Bluefin typically range from -0.01% to 0.05% hourly during normal market conditions, with extreme rates reaching 0.15% during Solana ecosystem rallies. Historical data shows funding spikes correlate with Jupiter DEX volume surges and major Solana DeFi protocol launches. The Sui blockchain's fast finality creates more responsive funding rate adjustments compared to Ethereum-based perp DEXs. Weekend funding rates often compress as institutional activity decreases, creating predictable arbitrage windows for retail traders."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Cross-Chain Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bluefin's SOL funding frequently trades at premiums to centralized exchanges due to Sui ecosystem growth driving native demand for SOL exposure. Typical arbitrage spreads range from 0.01% to 0.03% hourly, with occasional spikes to 0.08% during high volatility periods. The primary opportunity involves shorting SOL on Bluefin while longing on Binance or OKX to capture positive funding differentials. Settlement timing differences between Bluefin (hourly) and 8-hour CEX cycles create additional arbitrage complexity requiring careful position timing."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Sui network congestion during high activity periods can delay funding settlements, creating temporary basis risk for arbitrage positions. Bluefin's limited SOL/USDT open interest compared to major CEXs means large positions can significantly impact funding rates. Cross-chain bridge risks exist when transferring USDT between Sui and other networks for arbitrage execution. The Sui ecosystem's early stage creates additional smart contract risks, though Bluefin has maintained consistent uptime since launch with professional-grade security audits."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often does Bluefin settle SOL/USDT funding rates?","answer":"Bluefin settles SOL/USDT funding rates every hour on the hour, providing more frequent arbitrage opportunities compared to traditional 8-hour funding cycles. This hourly settlement reduces overnight funding risk but requires more active position management."},{"question":"What are typical funding rates for SOL/USDT on Bluefin?","answer":"SOL/USDT funding rates on Bluefin average 0.01-0.03% hourly during normal conditions, translating to 2.4-7.2% annually. During Solana ecosystem rallies, rates can spike to 0.1%+ hourly as demand for long exposure increases significantly."},{"question":"How does Bluefin's Sui infrastructure affect SOL trading?","answer":"Sui's parallel execution enables faster order matching and settlement for SOL perpetuals compared to Ethereum-based DEXs. The sub-second finality reduces slippage during volatile periods and enables more responsive funding rate calculations based on real-time market conditions."},{"question":"What's the minimum position size for SOL funding rate arbitrage on Bluefin?","answer":"Bluefin requires minimum trade sizes of $10 worth of SOL, making it accessible for smaller arbitrage strategies. However, profitable arbitrage typically requires positions above $1,000 to overcome the 0.02% taker fees and bridge costs for cross-exchange strategies."}]}]
